{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 24}After Jeconiah, the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah,{\super\cf2\fs24 1}with the princes, the craftsmen and the smiths, had beencarried from Jerusalem by Nebuchadrezzar, king ofBabylon, into exile in Babylon, Jehovah in a visionshowed me two baskets of figs set down in front of {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Jehovah\uc1\u8217*s Temple. One basket contained excellentfigs, like the figs that are first ripe: the figs in the otherwere very bad, so bad that they could not be eaten."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Then Jehovah said to me, "What seest thou, Jere-miah?" And I answered, "Figs \uc1\u8211* the good figs verygood, and the bad very bad, so bad that they cannot beeaten."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Thereupon this message came to me from Jehovah,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}"Thus saith Jehovah the God of Israel: As with thesegood figs, so will I regard with favour the exiles ofJudah, whom I have sent out of this place into the land {\super\cf2\fs24 6}of the Chaldeans. I will set Mine eyes upon them forgood, and bring them back to this land. I will not pullthem down, but I will build them; I will not pluck themup, but I will plant them; and I will give them a heartto understand me, that I am Jehovah. They shall beMy people and I will be their God, if they turn to Mewith all their heart.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}As for the figs that were too bad to eat, Thus saithJehovah: They are symbolic of the fate of Zedekiah,king of Judah, and his princes, and the survivors ofJerusalem that are left in this land, and those whose {\super\cf2\fs24 9}home is in the land of Egypt. For I will make theman object of consternation among every kingdom inthe world, a reproach and a proverb, a taunt and acurse, in every place to which I shall drive them; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and I will send among them sword, famine and pesti-lence, till they perish from the land that I gave to themand their forefathers.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs48 The Divine Judgment to be Executed by the Babylonians
upon Judah, upon the Neighbouring Nations, and upon the World at Large
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Prophetic Warning Disregarded by the People
 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 25}The message which came to Jeremiah concerning all{\super\cf2\fs24 1}the people of Judah in the fourth year of Jehoiakim,the son of Josiah, king of Judah, which was the first {\super\cf2\fs24 2}year of Nebuchadrezzar, king of Babylon \uc1\u8211* the mes-sage he delivered to all the people of Judah and allthe citizens of Jerusalem:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For twenty-three years \uc1\u8211* from the thirteenth yearof Josiah, the son of Amon, king of Judah, up to thisday \uc1\u8211* the message of Jehovah has been coming to me,and I have declared it to you early and late, but you {\super\cf2\fs24 4}have not listened. And early and late Jehovah hasbeen sending to you all His servants the prophets,through you have not listened nor inclined an attentive {\super\cf2\fs24 5}ear. My message was this: "If you abandon, everyman of you, your wicked ways and your evil behaviour,then you shall dwell for ever in the land which Jehovah,gave in the ancient time to you and your forefathers. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But do not indulge in the worship or service of othergods, and do not provoke Jehovah with the fabri-cations of your own hands: this can only injure your- {\super\cf2\fs24 7}selves." But you have not listened to me.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Judgment upon Judah and Her Neighbours

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Therefore thus saith Jehovah of Hosts: Because {\super\cf2\fs24 9}ye have not listened to My words, I will send andfetch a clan from the north, and I will bring themagainst this land and its inhabitants and against thesorrounding nation. I will devote them to destruc-tion so appalling that men shall hiss and revile them {\super\cf2\fs24 10}for ever; and I will banish form them the voice of mirthand gladness, the voice of bridegroom and bride, thesound of the millstones and the light of the lamp. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}This whole land shall be a waste and a horror, andthese nations shall serve the king of Babylon for seventyyears.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}When, however, seventy years are completed, I will punishthe king of Babylon, and that nation, saith Jehovah, for theirguilt, and also the land of the Chaldeans, which I will make {\super\cf2\fs24 13}desolate for ever; and I will bring upon that land all the wordsI have pronounced against it \uc1\u8211* everything prophesied byJeremiah against all the nations, that is recorded in this Book. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}They, yes they, shall be reduced to slavery at the hands ofmany nations and of great kings, and I will give them the rewardthat their acts and deeds deserve.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Cup of Jehovah\uc1\u8217*s Fury to be Drunk by all Nations

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}For thus said Jehovah, the God of Israel, to me,"Take from My hand this wine-cup of wrath, and giveit to all the nations to whom I send thee to drink from; {\super\cf2\fs24 16}and let them drink and reel in madness because of the {\super\cf2\fs24 17}sword that I will send among them." So I took thecup from the hand of Jehovah, and I gave it to all thenations to whom Jehovah had sent me, to drink from\uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Jerusalem and the cities of Judah, with her kings andprinces, to be made a desolation, a horror, a scorn, {\super\cf2\fs24 19}and a curse; Pharaoh, king of Egypt, with his {\super\cf2\fs24 20}ministers, his princes, and all his people, and allthe foreign folk; all the kings of the land of Uz, andall the kings of the land of the Philistines \uc1\u8211* Ashkelon, {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Gaza, Ekron, and the survivors of Ashdod; Edom, {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Moab, and Ammon; all the kings of Tyre and sidon;and the kings of the coast-land across the sea; {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Dedan and Tema and Buz, and all those that have the {\super\cf2\fs24 24}corners of their hair clipped; all the kings of NorthernArabia, and all the kings of the north, far and near,one with another, and all the kingdoms on the face ofthe earth; and after them shall the king of Sheshachdrink.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 27}Thou shalt say to them, Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts,the God of Israel: Drink yourselves drunk till ye fall inyour vomit, to rise no more, because of the sword that I {\super\cf2\fs24 28}shall send among you. If they refuse to take the cup fromthy hand to drink, then thou shalt say to them, Thus saith {\super\cf2\fs24 29}Jehovah of Hosts: Drink it you shall; for, if the citywhich is called by Mine own name is the first to feel theweight of My displeasure, how can you expect to goutterly unpunished? Nay, verily, ye shall not escape;for I am summoning the sword upon all the inhabitantsof the earth, saith Jehovah of Hosts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 30}As for thee, let thy prophetic message to them bethis:Jehovah will roar from on high,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
He will utter His voice from His holy abode;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Against His own fold He will mightily roar,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
He will lift a "hurrah" like the men at the vintage
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Against those that dwell on the earth, every one.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 31}Then din shall reach to the end of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For Jehovah doth hold a dispute with the nations;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Yeah, He with all flesh will contend in judgment,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And those that are base He will give to the sword.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 32}Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
See! misery spreadeth from nation to nation;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
From the uttermost corners of earth
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
There stirreth a mighty tempest.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 33}That day the slain of Jehovah shall lie
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
From one end of the earth to the other,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Unmourned, ungathered, unburied,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
As dung on the face of the ground.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 34}Howl, ye shepherds, and cry,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And roll you in ashes, ye lords of the flock;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For the days are ripe for your slaughter,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Like lambs that are doomed shall ye fall.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 35}No escape shall be left for the shepherds,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
No flight for the lords of the flock;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 36}O hark to the cry of the shepherds,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
The howl of the lords of the flock;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For Jehovah destroyeth their pasture.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 37}The meadows, so peaceful, are hushed
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
At the fierce hot wrath of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 38}The lions have left their covert,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For the land is become a desert,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Because of the cruel sword,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And because of His fierce hot anger.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs48 Jeremiah on Trial for his life
 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 26}In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim, the son of{\super\cf2\fs24 1}Josiah, king of Judah, the message which follows came {\super\cf2\fs24 2}(to Jeremiah) from Jehovah: Thus saith Jehovah,Take thy stand in the Temple court, and declare with-out reservation to all the people of Judah who are cometo worship in the Temple, the whole message that I {\super\cf2\fs24 3}have commissioned thee to declare. It may be thatthey will listen and severally abandon their wickedways: if they do, I will relent and not bring upon themthe calamity I am planning as penalty for their evil {\super\cf2\fs24 4}behaviour. This, then, is what thou art to say tothem, Thus saith Jehovah: If ye refuse to obey Me\uc1\u8211*to live in accordance with the law that I have set before {\super\cf2\fs24 5}you, and to listen, as ye have never yet listened, to thewords of My servants the prophets, whom early and {\super\cf2\fs24 6}late I have been sending to you \uc1\u8211* then I will make thisTemple like Shiloh, and as for this city, I will turn itinto an object of execration to every nation in the world.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Now the audience that listened to this message ofJeremiah\uc1\u8217*s in the Temple included not only the wholebody of the people, but the priests and the prophets {\super\cf2\fs24 8}as well. So when he had concluded the message whichJehovah had commissioned him to declare to the whole {\super\cf2\fs24 9}people, the priests and the prophets seized him. "Youmust die," they exclaimed; "for how dare youdeliver in the name of Jehovah such a message as this,that this Temple will meet the fate of Shiloh, and thatthis city shall become an inhabited desolation?"At this juncture all the people began to crowd roundJeremiah in the Temple.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Now echoes of this tumult having reached the earsof the countries of Judah, they proceeded from thepalace up to the Temple; and after they had takentheir seats at the entrance to the new gate of the Temple, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}the priests and the prophets addressed themselves tothe countries and the whole body of the people. "Thisman." they said, "is guilty of a capital offence; forhe has solemnly declared that this city is doomed\uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}you have heard him with your own ears. ThenJeremiah in his turn addressed himself to the courtiersand to the whole body of the people. "It is JehovahHimself," he said, "that has sent me to proclaim uponthis Temple and city the doom which you have just {\super\cf2\fs24 13}heard. If, however, you amend your life and con-duct, and listen to the voice of Jehovah your God, thenHe will relent and cancel His threat of catastrophe. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}As for myself, I am in your hands: deal with me as {\super\cf2\fs24 15}you think right and proper. But be very sure of this,that, if you put me to death, you will only be bringinginnocent blood upon yourselves, upon this city, andupon her people; for it is the simple truth that Jehovahhas sent me to deliver this message in your hearing." {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Thereupon, the courtiers and all the people said to thepriests and the prophets, "This man is not guilty ofany capital offence; for his message to us has behindit the authority of Jehovah our God."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Them some of the elders, rising to their feet, thus ad- {\super\cf2\fs24 18}dressed the people assembled: "In the days of Hezekiah,king of Judah," they said, "Micah of Moresheth wasprophesying; and this is what he said to all the peopleof Judah:Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts:Like a field shall Zion be ploughed,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And Jerusalem levelled to ruins;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And the Temple Mount shall become
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Like a thickly wooded height.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Did Hezekiah the king or the people of Judah dreamof putting him to death? Rather were they not so over-come by godly fear that they sued for the favour ofJehovah, with the result that He relented and cancelledHis threat of catastrophe? But look at us! Why, we areon the verge of involving ourselves in a great calamity."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Jeremiah, however, had (also) the support of Ahikam,the son of Shaphan, who saved him from being deliveredto the people for execution.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Fate of Urijah

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 20}There was another case of a man who deliveredprophetic messages in the name of Jehovah \uc1\u8211* Uriah,the son of Shemaiah, who belonged to Kiriath-jearim.Quite in the manner of Jeremiah, he too had pronounced {\super\cf2\fs24 21}the doom of this city and land. His message havingreached the ears of King Jehoiakim, with all the courtand the military officials, the king took steps to havehim put to death. Urijah, however, got wind of hispurpose, and in terror he took to flight, finally reaching {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Egypt; but King Jehoiakim despatched commis-sioners to Egypt \uc1\u8211* Elnathan the son of Achbor, and a few {\super\cf2\fs24 23}others \uc1\u8211* who removed him from Egypt and broughthim back to the presence of King Jehoiakim, whohad him slain with the sword, and his dead body flunginto the public burying-ground.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 No Hope of Speedy Release from Babylon

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs48 The Babylonian Yoke will not be soon or easily Broken
 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 27}In the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah, the son{\super\cf2\fs24 1}of Josiah, king of Judah, Jeremiah received from {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Jehovah the message which follows. Thus spokeJehovah: Make thongs and bars and put them on {\super\cf2\fs24 3}thy neck, and send a message to the kings of Edom,Moab, Ammon, Tyre, and Sidon, through their am-bassadors who have come to Jerusalem to Zedekiah, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}king of Judah, and bid them say to their masters,"Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts, the God of Israel: {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Convey this message to your masters. I have madethe earth, with man and beast on the face of it,by My great power and outstretched arm, and I give it {\super\cf2\fs24 6}to whomsoever I please. At the moment I have givenall these lands into the hands of Nebuchadnezzar, kingof Babylon, My servant; the beasts of the field alsohave I given him to serve him.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}All the nations shall serve him and his son and his grandson,till the time of his own land shall come \uc1\u8211* then many nationsand great kings shall make him serve.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}The nation and the kingdom which refuses to serveNebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon, and to put theirnecks to the yoke of the king of Babylon \uc1\u8211* that nation,saith Jehovah, I will punish with sword, famine andpestilence, till I have delivered them into his hands.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}As for yourselves, do not listen to your prophets,diviners, dreamers, soothsayers, or sorcerers, whoassure you that you will not be subject to the king of {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Babylon. It is a lie that they preach to you, and itwill end in your removal from your own land; for I {\super\cf2\fs24 11}will indeed drive you away and ye shall perish. Butthe nation that brings its neck to the yoke of the king ofBabylon and serves him, I will leave on their own soil,which they shall continue to till and occupy."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}A similar message I gave to zedekiah, king of Judah,"If,\uc1\u8217* said I, "you bring your neck to the yoke of theking of Babylon, and serve him and his people, you will {\super\cf2\fs24 13}be spared. Why should you and your people die by thesword, famine and pestilence, with which Jehovah hasthreatened the nation that refuses to serve the king of {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Babylon? Do not listen to the prophets when they tellyou that you will not be subject to the king of Babylon: {\super\cf2\fs24 15}they are preaching to you a lie. I have not sent them,saith Jehovah: it is a lie that they are preaching to youin My name, and it can only end in your being drivenout and perishing \uc1\u8211* you and the prophets that preachto you."
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}And the message that I gave to the priests and to allthis people was this: "Thus saith Jehovah: Do notlisten to the prophets when they tell you that the vesselsof the Temple will soon be brought back from Babylon. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}They are preaching to you a lie: do not listen to them.Serve the king of Babylon and you will be spared: {\super\cf2\fs24 18}why should this city become a ruin? But if they arereal prophets with a real message from Jehovah, letthem entreat Jehovah of Hosts not to allow the vesselsthat are left in the Temple and in the royal palace at {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Jerusalem, to be taken to Babylon. For thus saithJehovah of Hosts concerning the pillars and the seaand the stands and the rest of the vessels that are left {\super\cf2\fs24 20}in this city, which were not taken by Nebuchadnezzar,king of Babylon, when he carried Jeconiah, the son ofJehoiakim, king of Judah, with all the nobles of Judah {\super\cf2\fs24 21}and Jerusalem, from Jerusalem to Babylon. Yes,thus saith Jehovah of Hosts, the God of Israel, con-cerning the vessels that are left in the Temple and in {\super\cf2\fs24 22}the royal palace and at Jerusalem; To Babylonthey shall be brought, and there they shall remain tillthe day that I visit them, saith Jehovah; then I willbring them up and restore them to this place."
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs48 The Clash between the False Prophet and the True
 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 28}The same year, at the beginning of the reign of{\super\cf2\fs24 1}Zedekiah, king of Judah, in the fifth month of the fourthyear, Hananiah the son of Azzur, the prophet, whobelonged to Gibeon, addressed me as follows in theTemple in the presence of the priests and of all the {\super\cf2\fs24 2}people. "Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts, the God ofIsrael: \uc1\u8217*I have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Within two years\uc1\u8217* time I will bring back to this place allthe Temple vessels that Nebuchadnezzar, king ofBabylon took from this place and carried to Babylon; {\super\cf2\fs24 4}and Jeconiah, the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, andall the exiles of Judah that have gone to Babylon, Iwill bring back to this place, saith Jehovah; for I willbreak the yoke of the king of Babylon.\uc1\u8217*"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Then Jeremiah the prophet replied to Hananiah theprophet in the presence of the priests and of all thepeople that were standing in the Temple; and Jeremiah {\super\cf2\fs24 6}the prophet said, "Amen! Jehovah do so! MayJohevah fulfil your prophecy and bring back the Templevessels and all the exiles from Babylon to this place! {\super\cf2\fs24 7}I ask you, however to listen to this word that I amabout to speak in your hearing and in the hearing of all {\super\cf2\fs24 8}the people. From the beginning the prophets who pre-ceded you and me in their messages concerning many {\super\cf2\fs24 9}lands and mighty kingdoms, prophesied war. If aprophet prophesies peace, it is only when his word hasbeen fulfilled that you can be sure that he has had a real {\super\cf2\fs24 10}commission from Jehovah." Then Hananiah took the {\super\cf2\fs24 11}bar off Jeremiah\uc1\u8217*s neck, broke it, and declared in thepresence of all the people, "Thus saith Jehovah:\uc1\u8217*Within two years\uc1\u8217* time, I will similarly break theyoke of Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon, off thenecks of all the nations.\uc1\u8217*" Then Jeremiah the prophetwent away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}But after Hananiah had broken the bar off Jeremiah\uc1\u8217*sneck, there came to Jeremiah this message from {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Jehovah: "Go and say to Hananiah, Thus saithJehovah, The wooden bar you have indeed broken,but {\super\cf2\fs24 14}I will replace it with a bar of iron. For thus saithJehovah of Hosts, the God of Israel: The yoke that Iwill put on the necks of all these nations will be madeof iron \uc1\u8211* a yoke of service to Nebuchadnezzar, king ofBabylon: for serve him they shall. I have also given {\super\cf2\fs24 15}him the beasts of the field." Then Jeremiah said toHananiah, "Listen, Hananiah. You have no com- {\super\cf2\fs24 16}mission from Jehovah: you are making this peopletrust a lie. Therefore thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8217*Mark thiswell: I will dismiss thee from the face of the earth.This very year thou shalt die; for thy words are a {\super\cf2\fs24 17}disloyalty to Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*" And that very year, in theseventh month, the prophet Hananaiah died.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs48 Jeremiah Exhorts the Exiles to settle down in Babylon
 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 29}The following is a copy of the letter sent from{\super\cf2\fs24 1}Jerusalem by Jeremiah the prophet to the elders, thepriests, the prophets, and all the people, who had beencarried from Jerusalem by Nebuchadnezzar to exile in {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Babylon \uc1\u8211* after the surrender of Jeconiah the king,and the queen-mother, and the eunuchs, and the princesof Judah and Jerusalem, and the craftsmen and smiths\uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 3}the letter being sent by the hands of Eleasah the son ofShaphan and Gemariah the son of Hilkiah, who hadbeen despatched to Babylon to Nebuchanezzar, king ofBabylon, by Zedekiah, king of Judah:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}"Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts, the God of Israel, toall the exiles whom I have carried from Jerusalem to {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Babylon: Build houses and settle; plant gardensand eat the fruit of them; take wives and rear families; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}take wives also for your sons and give your daughtersto husbands, that they may have sons and daughters;increase your numbers and do not let them diminish. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}And strive for the welfare of the country to which Ihave brought you as exiles. Pray for it to Jehovah;for your own welfare and hers are bound up together. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}For thus saith Jehovah of Hosts, the God of Israel:Do not let yourselves be beguiled by the prophets anddiviners in your midst, and do not listen to the dreams {\super\cf2\fs24 9}they dream; for it is a lie that they preach to you inMy name \uc1\u8211* they have no commission from Me, saithJehovah.
