{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Purchase
 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 32}The message which came to Jeremiah from Jehovah{\super\cf2\fs24 1}in the tenth year of Zedekiah, king of Judah, which {\super\cf2\fs24 2}was in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadrezzar. At thattime the forces of the king of Babylon were investingJerusalem, and Jeremiah the prophet was confined to {\super\cf2\fs24 3}the guard-house of the royal palace, where Zedekiah theking had shut him up on account of his propheticpreaching. "What do you mean," he had demanded,"by an announcement of this kind: \uc1\u8217*Thus saithJehovah, Depend upon it, I will give this city into thehands of the king of Babylon, and he shall take it. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Nor shall Zedekiah, king of Judah, escape the hands ofthe Chaldeans; he will assuredly be delivered into thehands of the king of Babylon. He shall speak to him {\super\cf2\fs24 5}face to face, and see him eye to eye; and he shall bringZedekiah to Babylon, where he will remain till I visithim. Though you fight with the Chaldeans you shallhave no success.\uc1\u8217*"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Now there came to Jeremiah the following message {\super\cf2\fs24 7}from Jehovah: "Hanamel, the son of thine uncleShallum, is about to pay thee a visit, to request thee tobuy the land he holds at Anathoth; and he will urgethat, as thou art the next of kin, it is thy privilege and {\super\cf2\fs24 8}duty to receive it." And so it happened: my cousinHanamel paid me in the guard-house the visit Jehovahhad intimated, and said: "I want you to buy the landI possess at Anathoth; for you are the legal heir, andit is your duty to secure it \uc1\u8211* so buy it for yourself."Then I recognised that the message I had received was {\super\cf2\fs24 9}really from Jehovah. So I bought the land at Anathothfrom my cousin Hanamel, and I weighed out the money {\super\cf2\fs24 10}to him \uc1\u8211* seventeen silver shekels. Then I signed thedeed and sealed it, took witnesses, and paid him the {\super\cf2\fs24 11}money in full. I then took the purchase-deed\uc1\u8211*the one which was sealed and the one which was open\uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}and gave it to Baruch, the son of Neriah, the son ofMachesiah, in the presence of my cousin Hanamel, andof the witnesses who had signed the purchase-deed {\super\cf2\fs24 13}and of all the Jews in the guard-house. In theirpresence I then gave these instructions to Baruch: {\super\cf2\fs24 14}"Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts, the God of Israel:Take these deeds \uc1\u8211* this purchase deed which is sealedand this deed which is open \uc1\u8211* and put them in anearthenware jar, so that they may be preserved for a {\super\cf2\fs24 15}long time to come. For thus saith Jehovah of Hosts,the God of Israel: A time is coming when houses andfields and vineyards shall again be bought in this land."
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Prophet\uc1\u8217*s Prayer

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Now, after I had given the purchase-deed to Baruch,the son of Neriah, I prayed in these words to Jehovah: {\super\cf2\fs24 17}"Ah, Lord Jehovah! Thou, by Thy mighty power andoutstretched arm, hast made the heavens and the earth, {\super\cf2\fs24 18}and nothing is too hard for Thee. Kindness Thoushowest to thousands, and retribution for the guilt ofthe fathers thou bringest home to their children after {\super\cf2\fs24 19}them, Thou great and mighty God, great in purpose andmighty in action, whose eyes are open to all the ways ofmen, giving to each his deserts and the fruit of his deeds. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}In the land of Egypt Thou didst set in Israel andamong (other) men signs and wonders (which arecommemorated) unto this day, and so didst win for {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Thyself the renown that is Thine to-day; and Thoudidst bring Thy people Israel out of the land of Egyptby signs and wonders, with mighty hand out- {\super\cf2\fs24 22}stretched arm and terrors great; and Thou gavest themthis land which Thou didst swear to their fathers togive them \uc1\u8211* a land flowing with milk and honey \uc1\u8211* and {\super\cf2\fs24 23}they came in and took possession of it. But they wouldnot listen to Thy voice, nor live in accordance with Thylaw; they have left undone all that Thou didst com-mand them to do; and so Thou hast brought all thismisery upon them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Behold how the siege-mounds for storming the cityare already close upon it, and under the stress ofsword, famine and pestilence, the city is already as goodas given into the hands of the Chaldeans that are assail-ing it. What Thou hast threatened has come, as {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Thou Thyself seest. And it was Thou Thyself, OLord Jehovah, who didst command me to buy the land;(and this I have done), writing and sealing the deedand calling witnesses, though all the while the city isalready as good as delivered into the hands of theChaldeans."
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Divine Answer: First, Judgment for Sin

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 26}Then there came to Jeremiah the following message {\super\cf2\fs24 27}from Jehovah: I am Jehovah, the God of all flesh: is {\super\cf2\fs24 28}there anything too hard for Me? Therefore thus saithJehovah: Behold! I am about to deliver this city intothe hands of the Chaldeans and of Nebuchadrezzar, {\super\cf2\fs24 29}king of Babylon, and he shall take it. Yes, theChaldeans that are assailing this city shall come and setthis city on fire and burn it, with the houses on whoseroofs they have provoked Me by burning sacrifice tothe Baal and by offering drink-offerings to other {\super\cf2\fs24 30}gods; for, ever since their youth the people of Israeland Judah have done nothing but evil in My sight. {\super\cf2\fs24 31}From the day it was built up to this day, this city hasprovoked Me to remove it, in wrath and fury, out of {\super\cf2\fs24 32}My sight, for all the evil that the people of Israel andJudah have wrought to vex Me \uc1\u8211* themselves, with theirkings, princes, priests and prophets, with the men of {\super\cf2\fs24 33}Judah and the citizens of Jerusalem. They haveturned their backs to Me instead of their faces; andthough I taught them early and late, they would never {\super\cf2\fs24 34}listen or accept correction. The very House thatbears My name they have defiled by introducing {\super\cf2\fs24 35}into it their abominable worship. They have builtBaal sanctuaries in the Valley of the son of Hinnomfor the (fiery) consecration of their sons and daughtersto Molech, though this was no commandment ofMine \uc1\u8211* it never entered into My mind that they shoulddo this abomination, and thus involve Judah in sin.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Thereafter, Promise of Restoration

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 36}Now, therefore, Thus saith Jehovah, the God of Israel,concerning the city of which ye say that hunger,famine and pestilence have already as good as delivered {\super\cf2\fs24 37}it into the hands of the king of Babylon: See! I willgather them out of all the lands to which, in My greatwrath, anger, and fury, I have driven them, for I willbring them back to this place and settle them here {\super\cf2\fs24 38}securely; and they shall be My people, and I will be {\super\cf2\fs24 39}their God. A single heart I will give them, and a singleway (will I set before them), that they may hold Mein reverence for ever, and that they and their children {\super\cf2\fs24 40}after them may prosper; and I will make with theman everlasting covenant to follow them ceaselesslywith My blessing, and I will put the fear of Me in theirhearts, that they may follow Me without swerving. {\super\cf2\fs24 41}It will also be a joy to Me to do them good; andfaithfully, with all My heart and soul, I will plant them inthis land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 42}For thus saith Jehovah, As surely as I have broughtupon this people all this mass of misery, so surely will Ibring upon them all the blessings I promise them. {\super\cf2\fs24 43}In this land that ye call a desolation, forsaken of manand beast and delivered into the hands of the Chal- {\super\cf2\fs24 44}deans, fields shall be bought once more. Yes, menshall buy fields for money, subscribing and sealing thedeeds, and taking witnesses, in the district of Benjaminand the neighbourhood of Jerusalem and the cities ofJudah, in the cities of the hill country, the lowland,and the south. For I will restore their fortunes, saithJehovah.
